description: Driven insane by Dr. Freak's drugs, Batman goes on a rampage. Only two ex-cop mercenaries stand in the way of his run through Gotham City. "Freakout" finale.
name: Freakout Part 3 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

name: Red Knight,Black Night part 2:The Dragon

description: Drunk with power from one of the Dreamlord's own stones, Bridget's ex-lover pursues her ex-fiance from the Dreaming to the waking world, while Bridget and Matthew the Raven realize that romantic illusions may be extremely hazardous to one's health.
name: Weird Romance, Part Three
Book One

description: A hellish love triangle is formed when John Irons finds himself drawn to Amanda Quick, but she's also being courted by the diabolical Skorpio, a costumed menace with bio-mechanical weaponry.
name: It's French

description: With the mayoral election in high gear and ex-labor boss Derek Mancini looking like a shoe-in, Cross chases down his suspicions that his main squeeze's old man is also the secretive leader of the Flying Tigers gang. But first he and Blaze will have to contend with not one, but two, assassins out for revenge!
Denny's problems at school pale in comparison to one of Ninjak's deadliest foes, Karnivor, while Zeer starts to reveal his sinister plans.
As Tommy Lee Bones continues to wreak havok about New Orleans, Nettie and Jaunty approach Zero with their offer. Will he embrace the role of Shadowman? And even if he does, will he be enough?
name: Deadside Part Two

description: Becoming the permanent wearer of the X-O armor comes with a few changes for Donovan Wylie. A trip to the bottom of the ocean to investigate a downed submarine? No problem. Juggling the women in his life is a an entirely different story.
name: In Deep

description: OverviewA fantastic, hypnotic emerald has given Private Mann control over the rest of his Nazi infantry and the warrior women of Zuli. And, yet, this newfound power is pointless to him unless he can get back to civilization. Tarzan won't let him do that, and Tarzan cannot be controlled by the emerald. But there are other things which Mann can use to control the Lord of the Apes . . .
name: Legion of Hate (Part 4 of 4)

description: In the "Vampire Cat of the Geishu," Usagi's wanderings take him back to the Geishu Province and memories of the last time he was in the area. Usagi, Tomoe, and Gen were returning after the events in the "Dragon Bellow Conspiracy" (UY, Bk. 4) when they were invited to spend the night in the home of a noble woman. Too late, they find they were trapped by their hostess, a demon cursed to drink the blood of innocents.
name: The Obakneko of the Geishu Cla

description: As Bruce Wayne begins to romance radio talk-show host Vesper Fairchild, the Spectre searches for Batman. When the Spectre locates Batman in his Batcave, the Spectre realizes that Batman is not responsible for the deaths. Tracking down the true culprits, Batman disagrees with the Spectre's methods. Having a rare moment of faith, Batman begins to ask the Spectre a favor involving his parents, but the Spectre refuses to cooperate, stating that his knowledge involves the denizens of hell, and if he knew the answer, Batman would not like it.
name: The Spectre of Vengeance, Part 2: Mask of Guilt

description: The Mad Hatter dies in Arkham! But when trouble strikes Alice Pleasance, the Hatter's longtime obsession, Batman and Robin must get to the bottom of the mystery before it's too late to save the bride on her wedding day!
name: But a Dream

description:
Titania wonders when Faerie began to change, to feel less true. Selwyn, her maidservant, comes up to comfort her and briefly turns back into his true form as Auberon, before changing back to Selwyn before she notices. "Selwyn" tries to say that Auberon loves her, but Titania says she wasn't worthy of him.

Titania plans to read the Book of a Single Page for help, but first seduces "Selwyn," to Auberon's surprise.

Yarrow goes to Molly's tree house to find magical wards against her, due to the damage Molly has done since she caught on fire. Yarrow still feels loyalty to Molly and blames Titania for tricking her. The Amadan, eavesdropping, drops down behind her.

Molly and Taik walk along in the woods; she is no longer on fire. He is not a fan of his mother, Titania, and doesn't know why she turned him into a horse. Molly starts hearing voices; she takes medication to stop this back in the real world, but doesn't have the medication here. She starts to see Taik in an evil-looking form, but is it just her mental problems?

Amadan says the other fairies blame him for bringing Molly to Faerie in the first place (for their contest of fools, which never happened). A mob gathers at the bottom of the tree. Amadan, so brave before, now asks Yarrow to save him. She says she knows a way. He swears to do anything she says.

Titania goes to the Book and asks it what she must do. Stunned at the answer, she runs and asks for the guards.

Molly realizes that her Gran might have packed her medicine when she first sent her off, so long ago. She and Taik run off to the treehouse to get it. Taik stops her, and asks if she is really sick--maybe the voices and hallucinations are really just her magical fey nature, giving her insight into reality? As he asks, he looks more demonic again, and then like a horse's skull. She tells him to get away, and explodes in fire again.

Titania looks out from a tower and sees a black ship flying through the sky, as the Book said would happen. Three figures with white masks and chains walk out. They are Hell Lords. She says the contract was not broken, and it is not the time of the Tiend, so she wants to know why they are here. They say the contract was broken when someone whose life was given to them escaped from hell and came to Faerie.

This was Taik: they demand the return of him, and seven others, or they will take back that which Hell gave to Faerie.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Nine: Appearances

description: Catwoman's theft of an FBI satellite controller puts her in combat with Cybercat, She-Cat and a mysterious and lethal third party.
name: She-Cats Part 3: Cat Fights

description:
The Challengers fly to Dayton, Ohio, to investigate a corpse turned literally inside-out.

An energy field seemingly claims one of the Challengers. But things are far odder then they seem.
name: Threshold
Silent Weapons, Quiet Wars Conclusion

description: Santa Marta, California is Flash's new base of operations now, but that doesn't mean anything's calmed down for Wally! Because all of a sudden, Wally doesn't know reality from illusion as in that topsy-turvy world, the Flash finds he's become the slowest man alive!
name: Quicker than the Eye

description: The unexpected true king of Britain heads cross-country in search of the Holy Grail--all while thinking he's actually on a drug-induced trip! But when he finds the missing artifact, will he come to his senses before it falls into the wrong hands? "Last Man Standing" part 3.
name: Last Man Standing, Part 3 - Human Punk

description: Impulse's mother comes from the future to reclaim her son! Where has she been? What forced her to abandon Bart as an infant? Why has she waited so long to come for him? And will Bart abandon his life in the 20th Century to go home with mom?
name: Reunion

description: While in an underground military base, Ragged Robin, King Mob, Boy and Jolly Roger battle a billion Delta Force agents! Meanwhile, on the surface, Lord Fanny is busy with his own brand of magic when a menacing spirit causes chaos, and the evil dimensional dwarf Quimper takes a tragic tumble.
name: Black Science, Part Three: Sorted

description:
In the bloody climax to the 6-part ""Crusaders,"" Starr pulls off his boldest move yet while Allfather D'Aronique and his blessed child meet their fate and Jesse makes a last-ditch effort to save Cassidy.

Masada falls, between Starr's bombs and Jesse's talent for destruction; God leaves another message, this time with Cassidy.
name: And Justice For All (Crusaders Part 6)

description:
Spoiler tangles with The Ghost Dragons again while Lynx sets out to finish her off permanently.

Robin and Ariana brings issues with their relationship out into the open.
name: Nowhere fast

description: "The Scarlet Ghost" part 1! Truth is stranger than fiction in the seedy world of pulp magazines, as one publisher becomes a target for sabotage and murder and the Golden Age Sandman sets out to learn who's trying to stop the presses!
name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost: Act One of Four

story_arc_credits.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

description: In the immediate aftermath of losing his memories, the Shade wanders the London streets, and is met by a mysterious wealthy man with a sinister motivation.
name: A Family Affair, Piers: 1838

description: The Haunting of Jim Corrigan. Part 1: "Retribution." Part 1 of 5. The Spectre goes on a killing spree on death row at Attica prison, but finds an innocent man among them. Can he save him? Does he even care? Plus, Nate Kane has a strange dream and begins to suspect Jim Corrigan of murder.
name: The Haunting of Jim Corrigan, Part One: Retribution

description:
The Return of Bobo

Opal City is seen through the eyes of a time-lost figure from the past in this special issue that presents a spectacular starting point for new readers! Explore the world of Jack Knight and the entire STARMAN in this perfect introduction to the series!

After a quick recap from The Shade's Journal, we catch up with one Bobo Benetti. While the O'dares keep tabs on him, Jack and Ted learn the latest on Nash. Jack visits Charity. Together, Jack and Bobo face the Royal Flush Gang.
name: Welcome to the Revolution

description: Superman wakes up in a destroyed Metropolis! How did this happen? He finds out first-hand as time begins running backward to before the chaos! Can Superman save the day? Not if Mxyzptlk has anything to say about it.
name: Seonimod

description: Has it been ten years already?! Celebrating the 10th Anniversary of WONDER WOMAN'S re-launch, DC Comics presents a special-sized issue, featuring a cover by WW alumnus (and the man responsible for the first five years of the title George Perez, and pin-ups by former cover artists Brian Bolland and Nick Cardy. InsideDiana has been struck by a mysterious malady, her flesh-and-blood body is being turned slowly into clay! To discover the cause, Diana is forced to look back on her career as Wonder Woman and delve into the history of the Amazons and look into her own originwhere some previously unknown information lurks. Also includes the back-up tale Gateway or Boston!
name: Time Out of Mind

description:
Overview

While the police search Spawn's alleys looking for Cyan's kidnapper, Wynn directs a surveillance of his own on Terry with orders to find out why the police are looking for him. Spawn then finds Cyan and the Clown who taunts him into a battle. After Spawn uses up a portion of his energy to destroy the Clown, he brings Cyan to her parents.
name: Dwarfed

description:
Blood, death, revenge and madness - who says modern dance is dull? While Elektra opens her off-Broadway show, the being known as Architect, stung by Elektra's refusal to assassinate him, brings the curtain up on his own even more savage performance!

Elektra continues preparing for her dance role, while the Architect possesses a body in India and travels to Manhattan. Elektra continues to deal with the assassins who have descended on New York City and battles Razorfist.
name: Fury

description:
At Excalibur's headquarters, after a swordfighting drill with Nightcrawler, Colossus is approached by Amanda Sefton, who informs him, she's leaving Excalibur, but won't tell Kurt.

Meanwhile, in London, Brian Braddock battles the Dragons of the Crimson Dawn, three mystical beings who want to use Brian's power to expand the Crimson Dawn to Earth's dimension. Meggan lies unconscious as Spiral observes. Brian knocks out the massive six-armed Barak, but is hauled miles away by A'yin.

Back on Muir Isle, Kitty Pryde interrupts Pete Wisdom just as he deletes an email from an unrevealed female. Kitty then joins Rahne Sinclair for a girls' day out.

In London, Meggan regains consciousness in time to catch Brian who has just been hurled toward the ground by A'yin while she catches glimpses of a ghostly monk who also wears the mark of the Crimson Dawn.

Ra'al reminds Spiral of her obligations, and she replies by teleporting Ra'al and Brian elsewhere. Meggan tells Spiral they must contact Excalibur. Spiral agrees, all-too-willingly.
name: The Old Ways

description:
When her back is put agains the wall, Jubilee becomes unleashed! But who will pay the price?

Gen X drift across an ocean after they are freed from Black Toms prison, but cannot find land and despite all their powers, may well die from exposure. Jubilee makes a break from the forces of Operation: Zero Tolerance, but is re-captured after saving the life of one of her attackers. Sean is in a deep depression after the death of Emma and the disappearance of the kids, but Emma was only faking her death and returns telling him the kids are still alive and they will find them.
name: Adrift

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Overview

The war between Spider-Man and the Chameleon ends with a surprise twist involving to Mary Jane! The Legion of Losers is created by Gibbon, Grizzly, Kangaroo and Spot.
name: Kravinov's Revenge!

description: This is the story of really happened on Rigel VII. In the very first pilot of Star Trek ever Captain Christopher Pike tells the ships doctor how bad he has failed on his mission of Rigel VII and how he blamed himself for the deaths of his crew, and all the injured. If you look close you can even see the bandaged arm of Jose Tyler from the fight. The story is laid open on the pages of this book as Captain Pike and his crew struggle for survival as they are victims of an ambush of the Kaylar.
name: Our Dearest Blood

description: Due to crew being injured, Lt. Uhura is now responsible for the away mission. Can she deal with an alien intelligence and insubordination?
name: Message In A Bottle; Sins Of The Father

description: When the crew comes to fisticuffs with each other, you know it's time for a little R & R! It looks like the problem will be solved when the U.S.S. Voyager comes upon an M-class planet. But how can this vacation spot exist if all of the planets in that system were destroyed long ago? Maybe it can all be explained by the planet's population of ghosts!
name: Relicquest, Part One

description:
Overview

After the tragic events of Onslaught, a new hero team has emerged to fill the void of the lost heroes. The team calls themselves the Thunderbolts and they appear to stop the Rat Pack from looting the destroyed area. Their leader is Citizen V a relative to the World War Two Citizen V. After the Rat Pack is stopped from looting, they call the Wrecking Crew to assist in the fight with the Thunderbolts. They are defeated and the Thunderbolts help make repairs to the area. However there is a secret behind these heroes.
name: Justice... Like Lightning!
The Quick and  the Dead

description:
Nate Grey sails to Muir Island from mainland Europe, moors his sailboat, then climbs the cliff toward Excalibur's headquarters. As he ascends, he recalls his meetingto request help fromPeter Parkerat the Daily Bugle building. Peter recommends Nate seek out one of the X-teams to aid him with his waning telekinetic powers.
At the top of the cliff, Nate telepathicallyrenders himself invisible so as to pass by Nightcrawler, Amanda Sefton and Wolfsbane outside, then Kitty Pryde and Pete Wisdom within Excalibur's home. However, sensors have alerted Moira McTaggart to Nate's presence, and she brings him into her lab.
Since Nate was close to his dimension's Forge, Moira tries to contact X-Factor, but is told by government liason Val Cooper that X-Factor (including this Earth's Forge)are believed dead.
Meanwhile, under New York City, the Dark Beast, Havok and Fatale monitor Nate's whereabouts, as they make plans for the Brotherhood.
Back in her lab, Moira unexpectedly begins firing upon Nate with her weapon. Once Nate telekinetically stops her, she explains he's been repressing his own powers, not losing them; her 'attack' was meant to force Nate to reawaken his abilities.
As Nate stands on the cliff, preparing to depart, Havok and Fatale materialize in front of him.
name: Down to Earth

description: P.Q. Goybi's ship comes under attack as it closes in on the castle and the crew are forced to use an escape pod. Thankfully its got them close enough to their goal to reach it on foot.
Several different stories all told at once, all exploring the House of Secrets and its secret history!
name: Blueprint: Elevation A

description:
Roxy gets a tattoo. It's not revealed what the tattoo is of.

Keepers from I.O. attempt to capture Gen 13 and pursue them to their home. Anna engages the Keepers, giving the others a chance to escape. Anna detonates the home, sacrificing herself in the process.

Reprints the back-up stories that were originally in the Classic X-men issues #3-5 & #12:-

  1. Mouring
  2. The Big Dare
  3. Prison of the Heart
  4. A Fire In The Night
name: A Fire In The Night

description:
The Phalanx have infiltrated the X-Men by assuming the identities of several members. To save themselves, the team must allow their ship to be destroyed. Stranded in space, the X-Men must hatch a daring plan to survive.

In the sick bay aboard their cruiser in the Shi'ar Empire, the X-Men (Beast, Bishop, Rogue, Gambit and Joseph) treat Deathbird, the sole survivor of a starstation devastated by the Phalanx. Deathbird and Bishop are nearly attacked by two Phalanx posing as Gambit and Joseph, but she shoots them down.

Elsewhere on the ship, Phalanx have boarded and captured Gambit and Joseph. Rogue fights the aliens, but begins to succumb to a techno-virus, when Gambit breaks free and rescues her and Joseph.

In an interlude on Earth, Bastion arrives at his base with his captive, Jubilee [see Generation X #25].

Having defeated the boarders, the X-Men continue toward the heart of the empire, but their cruiser is destroyed by a Phalanx ship. The mutants and their allies, safely huddled in a pod held together by Joseph's power, drop to a planet with a Shi'ar outpost. From there, they teleport to the Shi'ar Throneworld.
name: Where No X-Man Has Gone Before!

description:
Aquaman faces a great white death when he battles for his life against a mind-controlled aquatic army!

Meeting with a Japanese dignitary, the Shark discusses terms in dealing with Aquaman. Meanwhile, the Sea KIng is dealing with his own issues. Due to aggressive use of his telepathy, Aquaman has undergone a physical mutation. His skin has become slightly scaly, and his teeth have noticeably sharpened. Dolphin is horrified at Aquaman's appearance. Though Dane Dorrance, of the Sea Devils, offers to conduct a scientific investigation into Aquaman's mutation, the Sea King refuses to undergo any tests, preferring to handle the matter personally. Aquaman takes his leave of the Sea Devils, but Dolphin refuses to go with him. The Shark negotiates with the artificial intelligence controlling the meteor ship, upon which the city of Poseidonis rests atop. The ship lowers Poseidonis back into the sea, allowing the Shark and his mutated shark minions to enter the city. Aquaman dismisses his condition as being simply stress related, but when the fish of the sea turn from him in terror, he has cause to reassess his situation. Meanwhile, at Star Beach, in California, the dismembered remains of an unknown man wash up on shore, terrifying the local lifeguard, along with several of the bathers. Aquaman returns to Poseidonis, only to find it partially submerged in the sea, and teeming with mutated shark men. Arriving at the royal palace, Aquaman discovers the Shark sitting on the throne. Flanking him are a pair of mutated shark men, that Aquaman recognizes from when they were simply sharks, Cron One-Eye, and a whale shark called Grifid.

The Shark has garnered a contract with the Japanese to cease their slaughter of sharks, dolphins, and whales in return for Poseidonis, and Aquaman, dead or alive. The Shark brings his psychic power to bear on the Sea KIng, unleashing a bolt of pure telepathic force at Aquaman. Though Aquaman is able to dodge the Shark's first volley, he soon finds himself swarmed by the Shark's minions. Enraged at the sharks' disloyalty to him, their king, Aquaman slashes Grifid's chest open. Grifid's blood floods the waters of the throne room, inciting the other shark men to frenzy. With their focus on devouring one of their own, Aquaman and the Shark are left alone in the palace. The Shark hurls the throne at Aquaman, then telepathically broadcasts pure, primal fear into the Sea King's mind. With Aquaman cowering in terror before him, the Shark pushes the Sea KIng into committing suicide. As Aquaman raises his own harpoon to his neck, he suddenly gives in to the dark temptation to aggressively attack with his own telepathy. The Shark is driven back by Aquaman's telepathic assault, then forcibly devolved by Aquaman's sheer force of will. Aquaman collapses on the throne room floor. Upon awakening he finds that his victory was not without cost to himself. Pushing his telepathic powers to such limits has caused the Sea King to mutate further, becoming far less human.
name: Shark Bait

description:
The stunning conclusion to the first story arc of the best-selling perennial title! How will The JLA respond to a threat that could destroy the world-and themselves? Read this issue and find out!

Everything looked lost but with Batman still fighting the JLA had a chance. Superman realizes he is being mind controlled and fights back. Martian Manhunter reveals that he has been under disguise and attacks Primaid. While doing so he releases the rest of the JLA and a fight between the JLA and the White Martians begins and ends. It is then left to the Martian Manhunter to sentence the White Martians to life out their lives (unknowingly) as humans, trapped in their own minds.
name: Invaders From Mars

description:
In a monastary inthe Alps, an Askani monk from the future is visited by the astral form of the priestess Sanctity. She reminds him of his mission to see Cable's 'destiny' fulfilled, a mission the monk is reluctant to see through.
In a New York nightclub, Cable and Storm stake out a benefit show by Lila Cheney, where a terrorist attack is expected. Callisto and Marrow appear, throwing the crowd into a panic, causing Storm to suffer a claustrophobic attack.
Not expecting Cable there, Callisto and Marrow leave via one exit, while he and Storm go outside to regroup. Callisto sends Marrow back in with a sound-sensitive bomb, set to go off during Lila's last number. As Cable tracks Marrow inside, Storm and Callisto battle on the rooftops. Cable overcomes Marrow, then throws the bomb to Lila, who teleports it across the galaxy to explode harmlessly. Callisto and Marrow escape in the confusion.
name: Tolerance

description: Dr. Killebrew explains to Deadpool and Siryn that Wades Healing factor is defective due to it being exposed to gamma radiation (which he came into contact in issue #1 (remember?)). But, there might be a way to stop Deadpool from dying. All theyll need is a sample of the incredible Hulks blood, which will stop the gamma particles from continuing to infect his body. The three of them ride to the Hulks new island. Once there, Deadpool starts batling with the jolly green giant. After a grueling match, Deadpool is able to cut the Hulk with a street sign, and steals a blood sample. Deadpool quickly escapes and meets back up with Siryn and Killibrew. Despite them noticing that somethings obviously not right with the Hulk, they return to Killibrew's lab. While there, Dr. Killebrew inoculates Deadpool. With the Hulks blood now floating inside him. Killebrew is confident that the procedure has been a success. Siryn believes that both Killebrew and Wade will put their past behind them. She tells them she believes in the both of them. Deadpool thanks Siryn for that. But, it will not prevent him from taking his revenge on Killebrew, and quietly holds a scalpel behind his back, ready to use it.
name: Why Is It, to Save Me, I Must Kill You?

description:
PKNA #4

Terremoto / Earthquake
name: Terremoto

description: Phoney and the townspeople reach the Dragon's Stair, a pass high in the mountains. Phoney gets the townsfolk to set up a dragon trap as he prepares to flee with his ill-gotten gains, but the plan becomes more complicated when the Great Red Dragon deliberately walks into the trap, courtesy of Ted. The townspeople urge Phoney to kill the trussed-up dragon, but just as he is about to reluctantly bring the knife down, Thorn arrives and stops him. She points out the columns of smoke rising from the valley; in their absence, the town has been attacked and burned by Rat Creatures. Suddenly another pack of Rat Creatures encounters the party, so Phoney frees the dragon. Thorn, with the four Veni Yan monks fighting alongside her, drives the Rat Creatures away. She instructs the townsfolk to arm themselves and head back to the town; war against the Rat army and their allies has begun.
name: Midsummer's Day

description: Powerless and alone, can Kyle survive his deadly game of cat and mouse with Fatality, a deadly opponent who has made a living assassinating members of the Green Lantern Corps.
name: Retribution, part 3

deck: Buzz, the demon from Linda's past, finally makes his move. His fiendish plan? One INCREDIBLY awkward family dinner at the Danvers house.
description: A clean-cut Buzz arrives at the Danvers home for his blind date with Linda, and proceeds to cause all manner of psychological havoc in "My Dinner With Buzz." Part 1 of 2, continued next issue.
name: My Dinner With Buzz

description: As Nightwing shook down various no-gooders, Angel Marin's body turned up, with it's head on backwards. Oracle gave Nightwing a name - Roland Desmond aka Blockbuster. He called some Titans buddies for info on him, and then tracked him down; Soames was at Blockbuster's side.
name: Rough Justice

description:
The entire Legion is back together again after being separated by time-but now they're trapped in the timestream and time is running out to save a comatose member!

The Legion is trapped in the timestream and must make due with what little resources they have to traverse time to build a means home.
name: No Exit

description:
Overview

Two days ago, the crew of a Chilean fishing vessel saw something fall from the sky. They were into the Humboldt current, watching the approach of a fast-moving weather front, when they heard a roar like a huge turbine in the sky. The rain swept over them, and through the sheets coming down through the clouds they saw a vision that at times took on material definition and flickered with an electricty of its own. Captain Cromartie has a pretty good idea what's down in those cold waters -- he's pretty sure he's fishing for Predators. But knowing what you're fishing for and knowing how to catch it are two totally different things.
A group of trapped citizens pass the time encountering various incidents where they saw or met Batman.
name: Stories

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: Bridget and Matthew arrive at Eve's cave, where they discover some surprising revelations about Bridget and her two suitors, and encounter the power of the Crawpock.
name: Weird Romance, Part Four

description:
Zombie humans are one thing, but Tommy Monaghan comes face-to-face with zombie seals, sharks and octopodes! Terrors from the deep arise in "Zombie Night at the Gotham Aquarium" Part 2!

The Gotham Aquarium is now full of bloodthirsty zombie animals. It's time to leave but the place is falling apart...and so is the team.
name: Zombie Night at the Gotham Aquarium, Part Two

deck: Supergirl battles Buzz's minion - Tempus Fugit.
description: Supergirl gets some unexpected help in her climactic battle with Tempus Fugit and Buzz in "Tempus Fugit." Part 2 of 2, continued from the previous issue.
name: Tempus Fugit
Book Two
The Closer

description: Steel's search for his kidnapped boss takes him to Africa, where only one man can help him pull off a dangerous rescue...the man called The Question.
name: The Gambler

description: Ninjak invades the offices of Acclaim Entertainment, as he begins his search for the truth about his powers and finds even more questions!

Jaunty takes Zero on his first journey through the Deadside, and the trip may reveal the answers to the many questions of his past. It Is Nettie's job to prepare the new Shadowman, but what secrets is she be hiding herself?
name: Deadside Part Three

description: Jacob Revere and R.A.G.E. are preparing to strike another blow to the U.S., and they have their sights set on Los Angeles. Having defeated them once before, will Donovan and the X-O armor be able to best the terrorist threat a second time?
name: Special Delivery

description:
Overview

In The Freebooters, Axus and his band, hungry for action, raid the Kalif's own palace, only to find things there unsettlingly bizarre. Meanwhile, the situation is getting out of hand back at The Ram and the Peacock. In The Paradoxman, Tristan Caine's treatment at the hands of his increasingly strange psychoanalyst pushes him to the edge -- which way will he fall? In Young Gods, we return to All-Worlds to find Otan and Queen Organa at increasing odds over the intended wedding of Heros and Celestra, while the evil Grand Vizier manipulates the hapless cherubs into doing his very dirty work. Join captivated readers across the globe for the seventh amazing issue of Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER, an omnibus of wonder that delivers comics entertainment at its best.

OverviewBeasts, savages, natural disasters -- these are the threats of the jungle, the things Tarzan has learned to control. But there is nothing natural about his current quarry. In turn-of-the-century Paris, the Lord of the Jungle faces a masked, tuxedo-clad assailant who carries off women; a beast with the trappings of "civilization." A phantom of the opera.
name: Le Monstre (Part 1 of 2)

description:
Overview
The mournblade Stormbringer climbs from its scabbard and stands in Elric's hand, waiting in anticipation for the new souls it might drink. Forged by Chaos to vanquish Chaos, it prepares to fulfill its ultimate destiny, as Elric prepares to fulfill his: He must destroy the Dukes of Hell. And what a battle it shall be, for the Dukes of Hell must surely know their turncoat servant comes to fight them!
name: Jagreen Lern and the City of Screaming Statues

description:
Overview

The serial killer known as Faceless begins murdering Gotham's citizens, apparently at random, and then removing their faces. Batman must stop this crime spree before more innocents die.

Joseph Zedno is just your regular mailman, visiting door to door delivering parcels and letters to the locals. Little do they know that beneath the surface lies a psychotic man who wants to be more than just a faceless nobody.

Meanwhile, Bruce Wayne strengthens a budding relationship with Vesper Fairchild, whilst tracking down a series of suspicious murders as Batman.
name: Faceless, Part 1: Murdicide

description: The Joker is in a slump and nothing that Harley Quinn can do, no matter how ingeniously evil, seems to be able to put a smile on the face of the Clown Prince of Crime. But maybe a captured Batman could put a smile on his face.
name: Joker's Last Laugh!

description:
Huon, a strange being known by many aliases, celebrates the end of one of them by dancing on the point of a needle, then enters its head and transforms into a fairy.

Tim, who has not appeared for a couple issues, and was last seen wandering the desert and meeting with Crazy Lightning, has randomly appeared in another realm, without knowing how or why. He is stuck on an island, and whenever he tries to get off, he just ends up back there again--but unknown to him, statues of himself, from every escape attempt, litter the far shore.

Members of Faerie surround the tree where the Amadan is holed up. They are angry at the destruction caused by Molly's burning, and are adrift in their identities, often without their glamours that make them seem more wonderful than they really are.

Yarrow flies out above the mob, showing them the head of Amadan--she tricked him into turning himself into stone.

She sees the ship from Hell, filled with demons, but doesn't understand why they are here because it is not the time of the Teind.

Titania confronts them. They want recompense for Taik, her son, who was supposed to be their prisoner, but is now returned to human form with Molly. The demons want her to refuse, so they can destroy Faerie, which they say once belonged to Hell.

However, Titania says she is not afraid of them. She is preparing for battle--but against the Leveller. Hearing this, the demons race back to their ship, but it won't fly away.

Molly has been overcome by her faerie fire, and can't see Taik, who circles her, taunting her. He has been taken over by, or is transforming into, a spirit that manifests itself as a skeletal horse. He still wants her to marry him, for her power. He wants revenge on Titania, but is also happy to kill her.

Yarrow appears, and invisibly tells Molly she will help.

Huon appears in Tim's boat in his Faerie form. He takes Tim's key (the key of worlds, gained in the original Books of Magic miniseries #3, and rarely if ever seen since), and tells him that Openers like Tim, and Levellers like himself, do what they must, and that right now, they are imprisoned, and must find a way out.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Ten: Reasons to be Stone

description:
An enemy of Catwoman's hires the nine best assassins in the world to kill the Feline Fatale.

9 Contracted hit"men" are paid to kill Catwoman with the assistance of Zee. Little do they know Zee has an ulterior motive.
name: Nine Deaths of the Cat
